WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.827
Myocarditis progresses through three distinct phases.

00:00:02.827 --> 00:00:06.126
In the acute phase — the first

00:00:06.126 --> 00:00:09.424
two weeks — viral entry triggers direct

00:00:09.424 --> 00:00:12.723
myocyte lysis, cytokine storm, and innate immune

00:00:12.723 --> 00:00:13.194
activation.

00:00:13.194 --> 00:00:16.492
The subacute phase follows with lymphocytic and

00:00:16.492 --> 00:00:19.320
macrophage infiltration causing T-cell mediated cytotoxicity.

00:00:19.320 --> 00:00:22.618
The chronic phase, extending beyond two weeks,

00:00:22.618 --> 00:00:25.917
shifts to autoimmune destruction — with aberrant

00:00:25.917 --> 00:00:29.215
HLA expression on myocytes perpetuating inflammation and

00:00:29.215 --> 00:00:31.100
driving adverse cardiac remodeling.
